From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Subject: [PATCH] drm/vkms: allow cloning the virtual and writeback encoders

VKMS leaves possible_clones unset on both its virtual output encoder and
the writeback connector's internal encoder. drm_mode_config_validate()
then fixes each up to its own bit only, so any atomic modeset that puts
both connectors on the CRTC (encoder_mask 0x3) fails the valid-clone
check in drm_atomic_helper_check_modeset() with EINVAL:

  [drm:drm_atomic_helper_check_modeset] crtc38 failed valid clone check for mask 0x3

This makes it impossible to capture the CRTC via the writeback connector
while a client drives the virtual output - the exact use case of a
writeback-based display bridge (compositor renders to VKMS, bridge
forwards frames to a physical display).

Declare the two encoders as clones of each other so both connectors can
be active on the CRTC at the same time.

Applies on top of 0002 (default mode patch).

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/vkms/vkms_output.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/vkms/vkms_output.c
@@ -128,8 +128,24 @@
 
 	if (vkmsdev->config->writeback) {
 		writeback = vkms_enable_writeback_connector(vkmsdev);
-		if (writeback)
+		if (writeback) {
 			DRM_ERROR("Failed to init writeback connector\n");
+		} else {
+			/* Allow the virtual and writeback encoders to be
+			 * active on the CRTC simultaneously, so a writeback
+			 * capture can run while a client drives the output.
+			 * Without this, drm_mode_config_validate() fixes up
+			 * possible_clones to self-only and any modeset with
+			 * both connectors attached fails the valid-clone
+			 * check in drm_atomic_helper_check_modeset().
+			 */
+			struct drm_encoder *wb_enc = &output->wb_connector.encoder;
+			u32 clones = drm_encoder_mask(encoder) |
+				     drm_encoder_mask(wb_enc);
+
+			encoder->possible_clones = clones;
+			wb_enc->possible_clones = clones;
+		}
 	}
 
 	drm_mode_config_reset(dev);
